1053
01:29:38,039 --> 01:29:40,064
Right in the middle of winter.

1054
01:29:40,541 --> 01:29:41,906
How was it?

1055
01:29:43,311 --> 01:29:45,438
I like being at sea.

1056
01:29:54,288 --> 01:29:57,917
Kid's come a long way
in the last few days, ain't he?

1057
01:30:25,286 --> 01:30:27,345
Let's get this over with.

1058
01:30:59,120 --> 01:31:02,283
He don't stand a chance
in Portsmouth, you know.

1059
01:31:03,124 --> 01:31:05,092
You know that, don't you?

1060
01:31:06,727 --> 01:31:10,788
Goddamn grunts kicking the shit
out of him for eight years.

1061
01:31:15,269 --> 01:31:17,430
He don't stand a chance.

1062
01:31:17,972 --> 01:31:20,099
I don't want to hear about it.

1063
01:31:23,711 --> 01:31:26,703
"Maggot" this. "Maggot" that.

1064
01:31:28,316 --> 01:31:31,217
Marines are really assholes,
you know that?

1065
01:31:33,955 --> 01:31:38,051
It takes a certain kind of a sadistic
temperament to be a Marine.

1066
01:32:57,238 --> 01:32:58,967
What the fuck's he doing?

1067
01:33:00,942 --> 01:33:02,637
Hey, Meadows!

1068
01:33:12,353 --> 01:33:13,752
What's he doing?

1069
01:33:16,324 --> 01:33:17,621
"Bravo...

1070
01:33:17,959 --> 01:33:19,358
...Yankee...

1071
01:33:19,594 --> 01:33:22,427
...Bravo, Yankee.
Bye-bye. End of the word."

1072
01:33:22,630 --> 01:33:25,463
Hey, this son of a bitch
is running away!

1073
01:33:26,033 --> 01:33:27,625
Halt, you son of a bitch!

1074
01:33:39,814 --> 01:33:42,647
Halt! You motherfucker!

1075
01:33:43,150 --> 01:33:44,310
Buddusky, don't!

1076
01:33:44,518 --> 01:33:45,348
Don't!

1077
01:33:49,523 --> 01:33:51,491
Goddamn, I lost my fucking shoe!

1078
01:34:10,011 --> 01:34:11,376
Let me go!

1079
01:34:12,513 --> 01:34:13,844
Buddusky, don't!

1080
01:34:14,048 --> 01:34:16,346
Let me go, you bastard!

1081
01:34:34,301 --> 01:34:36,929
Please let me go!

1082
01:34:53,187 --> 01:34:55,348
I lost my fucking shoe!

1083
01:36:47,401 --> 01:36:50,893
Baker, Mooney, prisoner from Norfolk,
on the double!

1084
01:37:35,082 --> 01:37:37,516
Where'd you get the idea
that wearing an armband...

1085
01:37:37,718 --> 01:37:40,380
...and a sidearm entitles you
to abuse a prisoner?

1086
01:37:42,489 --> 01:37:44,389
They teach you that in the Navy?

1087
01:37:45,359 --> 01:37:47,452
Or was that your idea of a good time?

1088
01:37:48,963 --> 01:37:49,827
I guess.

1089
01:37:50,030 --> 01:37:52,260
You guess what, sailor?

1090
01:37:55,569 --> 01:37:57,935
- Nothing.
- Nothing?

1091
01:37:59,039 --> 01:38:00,768
Nothing, sir.

1092
01:38:02,710 --> 01:38:06,441
- Did the prisoner offer any resistance?
- No, sir.

1093
01:38:09,116 --> 01:38:10,606
Did he try to escape?

1094
01:38:14,154 --> 01:38:15,678
Not exactly.

1095
01:38:18,559 --> 01:38:22,427
That's a little vague.
Either he did or didn't. Which is it?

1096
01:38:26,000 --> 01:38:29,026
Don't look at him
for the answer. Which is it?

1097
01:38:32,006 --> 01:38:33,906
- He didn't.
- He didn't what?

1098
01:38:35,676 --> 01:38:37,803
He didn't try to escape.

1099
01:38:41,348 --> 01:38:43,782
He didn't try to escape, "sir."

1100
01:38:46,520 --> 01:38:49,182
He didn't try to escape, sir.

1101
01:39:00,901 --> 01:39:02,425
You haven't left yet.

1102
01:39:03,070 --> 01:39:04,230
Sir?

1103
01:39:04,772 --> 01:39:08,708
Your orders weren't endorsed. According
to this, you're still in Norfolk.

1104
01:39:08,909 --> 01:39:10,501
Well, we're standing here.

1105
01:39:10,711 --> 01:39:11,871
It's not our fault.

1106
01:39:12,079 --> 01:39:13,239
You haven't left yet.

1107
01:39:13,914 --> 01:39:16,041
- You haven't left!
- That's not our fault!

1108
01:39:16,550 --> 01:39:19,678
Look, sir. We both got
a lot of time in.

1109
01:39:20,054 --> 01:39:21,544
What's that supposed to mean?

1110
01:39:22,089 --> 01:39:25,388
Too much time to be hard-ass
because some dude in Norfolk...

1111
01:39:25,592 --> 01:39:27,719
...forgot to endorse our orders.

1112
01:39:30,564 --> 01:39:32,156
You're asking for trouble.

1113
01:39:32,566 --> 01:39:34,397
I'm asking to see the XO.

1114
01:39:35,636 --> 01:39:36,898
Deep trouble!

1115
01:39:38,272 --> 01:39:39,204
No.

1116
01:39:40,708 --> 01:39:43,939
We ain't about to say
anything else until we see the XO.

1117
01:40:09,737 --> 01:40:11,261
Get the hell out of here.

1118
01:40:23,984 --> 01:40:26,145
You're supposed to pull a few copies.

1119
01:40:36,530 --> 01:40:38,464
Goddamn grunts!

1120
01:40:38,899 --> 01:40:40,992
Think they can get away with anything!

1121
01:40:41,502 --> 01:40:44,335
Telling me how to do my job.
I know my job.

1122
01:40:44,538 --> 01:40:48,702
I know my goddamn job better than
anybody else in the goddamn Navy!

1123
01:40:50,411 --> 01:40:52,777
We really told him though, didn't we?

1124
01:40:52,980 --> 01:40:54,811
Trying to ream our ass...

1125
01:40:55,015 --> 01:40:58,416
...and he don't even have sense
to pull a few goddamn copies!

1126
01:40:58,619 --> 01:41:00,780
Bunch of candy-asses!

1127
01:41:02,056 --> 01:41:05,321
I hate this motherfucking,
chicken shit detail.

1128
01:41:09,997 --> 01:41:11,555
Where are you going?

1129
01:41:11,965 --> 01:41:14,126
- Norfolk.
- I mean now.

1130
01:41:15,469 --> 01:41:19,098
I don't know. Stop off
in Baltimore maybe. You?

1131
01:41:20,174 --> 01:41:22,335
Back to New York, I guess.

1132
01:41:24,244 --> 01:41:25,677
See you in Norfolk.

1133
01:41:26,380 --> 01:41:29,747
Yeah. Maybe our fucking orders
have come through.


